    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="521"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Marshal <persName corresp="#p_SIV1" type="from"
                            >Stalin</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d521fn1">Sent via the Soviet Embassy, Washington.</note>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">Translation</p>
                <p>Personal and Secret Message to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                        >Roosevelt</persName> From Premier <persName corresp="#p_SIV1"
                        >Stalin</persName>
                </p>
                <p>I thank you for Your letter which Your Ambassador has extended to me on December
                        18th.<note n="2" xml:id="d521fn2">The letter from <persName
                            corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> dated December 3, 1943, <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_785">p. 785</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I am glad that fate has given me an opportunity to render you a service in
                    Teheran. I also attach important significance to our meeting and to the
                    conversations taken place there which concerned such substantial questions of
                    accelerating of our common victory and establishment of future lasting peace
                    between the peoples.<note n="3" xml:id="d521fn3">For a further reference, in the
                        post-Conference <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>–<persName
                            corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName> correspondence, to the cooperative
                        spirit which prevailed at Tehran, see <hi rend="italic">
                            <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName>’s Correspondence</hi>,
                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 119.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-20">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">December</hi> 20, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
